A Presidential aspirant, under the platform of the African Action Congress, AAC, Omoyele Sowore, on Saturday, said some members of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, will manage the All Progressives Congress, APC, after the latter’s national convention. Sowore said the APC convention is a gathering of some of the most wicked, dishonest, and unjust politicians in the world. In a tweet, Sowore wrote: “#APCConvention @OfficialAPCNg is the convening of the some of the most corrupt, incompetent, wicked, unjust and dishonest men and women politicians the world has ever known! “And just so that you understand what we’ve being saying, @OfficialPDPNig will now manage @OfficialAPCNg.” The APC national convention is taking place at the Eagles Square in Abuja. President Muhammadu Buhari is said to have endorsed Senator Adamu as APC’s next Chairman. Buhari’s choice of Adamu was disclosed by the Governor of Plateau State, Simon Lalong. To this end, other chairmanship aspirants have stepped down for Adamu.